ps%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998984a156648bc16a89a1f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221590%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatthew%20McConaughey%3Cp%3EKarwai%20Tang%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMatthew%20McConaughey%20and%20Timoth%C3%A9e%20Chalamet%20discussed%20AI%20during%20a%20televised%20town%20hall%20event.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMcConaughey%20said%20actors%20need%20to%20protect%20their%20likeness%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMcConaughey%20has%20secured%20eight%20trademarks%20related%20to%20his%20likeness.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20award%20for%20Best%20Actor%20goes%20to%E2%80%A6%20an%20AI%20model%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etrained%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatthew-mcconaughey-career-advice-going-to-film-school-new-book-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMatthew%20McConaughey%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20AI%20actors%20usurping%20human%20actors%20may%20sound%20far-fetched%20now%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20future%20that%20McConaughey%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Cem%3Ereal%3C%2Fem%3E%20McConaughey%20%E2%80%94%20believes%20emerging%20talent%20should%20prepare%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20it%20may%20be%20for%20you%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20enough%20to%20sit%20on%20the%20sidelines%20and%20make%20the%20moral%20plea%20that%20'no%2C%20this%20is%20wrong!'%26quot%3B%20McConaughey%20said%20during%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftimothee-chalamet-snl-oscar-awards-guerrilla-marketing-campaign-lime-bike-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETimoth%C3%A9e%20Chalamet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20going%20to%20last.%20There's%20too%20much%20money%20to%20be%20made%2C%20and%20it's%20too%20productive.%20It's%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20Chalamet%20spoke%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-investors-ai-hollywood-pitch-decks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20in%20the%20entertainment%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20students%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20during%20a%20CNN%20and%20Variety%20Town%20Hall%20event.%20The%20town%20hall%20will%20air%20on%20Saturday%20at%207%20p.m.%20ET%20on%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20conversation%2C%20McConaughey%20urged%20students%20to%20pursue%20legal%20protections%20for%20their%20likeness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20say%2C%20own%20yourself%2C%20voice%2C%20likeness%2C%20etc.%20Trademark%20it!%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcConaughey%20said%20doing%20so%20will%20give%20people%20more%20control%20over%20their%20branding%20and%20the%20opportunity%20to%20receive%20fair%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20%E2%80%94%20not%20if%20it%20comes%20%E2%80%94%20no%20one%20can%20steal%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20McConaughey%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20come%20to%20you%20and%20go%2C%20'Can%20I%3F'%20Or%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20in%20breach.%20And%20you'll%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20be%20your%20own%20agency%20and%20go%2C%20%26quot%3Byeah%2C%20for%20this%20amount%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20'no.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20McConaughey%20has%20already%20taken%20precautions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BInterstellar%26quot%3B%20actor%20had%20eight%20trademark%20applications%20approved%20over%20the%20last%20several%20months%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal.%20That%20included%20his%20iconic%20%26quot%3BDazed%20and%20Confused%26quot%3B%20catchline%2C%20%26quot%3Balright%2C%20alright%2C%20alright!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20team%20and%20I%20want%20to%20know%20that%20when%20my%20voice%20or%20likeness%20is%20ever%20used%2C%20it's%20because%20I%20approved%20and%20signed%20off%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20McConaughey%20told%20the%20Journal.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20create%20a%20clear%20perimeter%20around%20ownership%20with%20consent%20and%20attribution%20the%20norm%20in%20an%20AI%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20McConaughey%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20world%20where%20we're%20watching%20everybody%20scramble%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20about%20AI%20misuse%2C%20we%20have%20a%20tool%20now%20to%20stop%20someone%20in%20their%20tracks%20or%20take%20them%20to%20federal%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcConaughey%20is%20also%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvoice-cloning-startup-elevenlabs-raising-funding-valuation-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvestor%20in%20Eleven%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20AI-powered%20voice%20generation%20platform.%20More%20recently%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20that%20McConaughey%20is%20using%20its%20tech%20to%20create%20a%20Spanish-language%20version%20of%20his%20newsletter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatthew-mcconaughey-trademark-likeness-ai-hollwood-actors-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771670941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998984a156648bc16a89a1f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatthew-mcconaughey-trademark-likeness-ai-hollwood-actors-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Matthew%20McConaughey%20and%20Timoth%C3%A9e%20Chalamet%20discussed%20AI%20in%20the%20entertainment%20industry%20with%20college%20students%20during%20a%20CNN%20and%20Variety%20Town%20Hall%20event.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ledmonds%40businessinsider.com%20(Lauren%20Edmonds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatthew-mcconaughey-trademark-likeness-ai-hollwood-actors-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20high-earners%20are%20using%20real%20estate%20and%20a%20little-known%20rule%20to%20slash%20their%20tax%20bills%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6853089f3d5881a51c1bb20c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKenji%20Asakura%20and%20Letizia%20Alto%20are%20the%20co-creators%20of%20Semi-Retired%20MD.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20a%20little-known%20IRS%20designation%20called%20real%20estate%20professional%20status%2C%20or%20REPS.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20allows%20qualifying%20investors%20to%20use%20real%20estate%20losses%20to%20offset%20W-2%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20you%20or%20your%20spouse%20qualifies%20for%20REPS%2C%20it%20can%20reduce%20or%20even%20eliminate%20your%20tax%20liability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Dr.%20Jill%20Green%20watched%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20her%20physician's%20salary%20eaten%20up%20by%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20paying%20a%20ton%20in%20taxes%20and%20still%20writing%20a%20check%20for%20a%20hefty%20five-figure%20amount%20every%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20started%20investing%20in%20real%20estate%20about%20six%20years%20ago%20to%20create%20an%20additional%20revenue%20stream%2C%20she%20learned%20about%20a%20little-known%20IRS%20designation%20called%20real%20estate%20professional%20status%2C%20or%20REPS.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20strategy%20some%20tax%20experts%20have%20nicknamed%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-strategies-for-marital-loophole-real-estate-investors-save-taxes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarital%20loophole%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20allows%20qualifying%20investors%20to%20use%20real%20estate%20losses%20to%20offset%20W-2%20income%2C%20something%20most%20high%20earners%20can't%20typically%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20Green%20and%20other%20couples%20are%20using%20it%20to%20significantly%20shrink%20their%20tax%20bills%20while%20growing%20their%20rental%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227831829f-10eb-4dac-bd0e-5c66df06a52f%5C%22%3EWhy%20rental%20losses%20usually%20don't%20help%20high%20earners%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20normal%20IRS%20rules%2C%20rental%20real%20estate%20is%20considered%20a%20passive%20activity.%20That%20means%20rental%20losses%20can%20offset%20rental%20income%2C%20but%20they%20cannot%20offset%20W-2%20income%2C%20such%20as%20a%20physician's%20or%20accountant's%20salary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20you're%20a%20doctor%20earning%20%24250%2C000%20and%20your%20rental%20property%20shows%20a%20%24150%2C000%20loss%20on%20paper%2C%20you're%20still%20taxed%20on%20the%20full%20%24250%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20small%20exception%3A%20a%20%2425%2C000%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20allowance%26quot%3B%20for%20long-term%20rental%20losses%2C%20but%20it%20phases%20out%20between%20%24100%2C000%20and%20%24150%2C000%20of%20income%20and%20disappears%20entirely%20above%20%24150%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20high-income%20earners%2C%20that%20benefit%20isn't%20an%20option.%20If%20you're%20making%20over%20%24150%2C000%20and%20you%20want%20to%20use%20rental%20losses%20to%20offset%20W-2%20income%2C%20either%20you%20have%20to%20be%20a%20real%20estate%20professional%2C%20or%20you%20have%20to%20be%20married%20to%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20the%20%26quot%3Bmarital%20loophole%26quot%3B%20comes%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2243516fe4-e314-454f-848c-f734d5698e7a%5C%22%3EHow%20REPS%20works%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20spouse%20qualifies%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%20estate%20professional%2C%26quot%3B%20rental%20losses%20are%20no%20longer%20treated%20as%20passive.%20They%20become%20active%20losses%2C%20meaning%20they%20can%20offset%20active%20income%2C%20including%20W-2%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20continue%20to%20have%20your%20high%20W-2%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20CPA%20and%20real%20estate%20investor%20Amanda%20Han%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20long%20as%20your%20spouse%20is%20a%20real%20estate%20professional%2C%20then%20the%20rental%20losses%20can%20offset%20both%20of%20your%20incomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELetizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%2C%20both%20physicians%20who%20later%20scaled%20back%20their%20hospital%20work%20after%20building%20a%20large%20rental%20portfolio%2C%20said%20they%20used%20this%20strategy%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-income-tax-strategy-benefit-losses-reps-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bzero%20out%26quot%3B%20their%20income%20taxes%20for%20seven%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20accelerate%20their%20path%20to%20financial%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%20hinges%20on%20generating%20tax%20losses%2C%20not%20necessarily%20losing%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20common%20in%20real%20estate%20to%20produce%20positive%20cash%20flow%20while%20showing%20a%20loss%20on%20your%20tax%20return.%20That's%20largely%20because%20of%20depreciation%2C%20a%20non-cash%20deduction%20that%20allows%20owners%20to%20write%20off%20a%20portion%20of%20a%20building's%20value%20each%20year%2C%20as%20well%20as%20deductible%20expenses%20like%20renovations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20Asakura%20qualified%20for%20REPS%2C%20the%20couple%20leaned%20into%20upgrades.%20On%20paper%2C%20those%20renovation%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20combined%20with%20depreciation%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20generate%20sizable%20losses.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20improvements%20increased%20the%20properties'%20value%20and%20allowed%20them%20to%20raise%20rents.%20So%2C%20they%20were%20improving%20their%20portfolio%20and%20boosting%20cash%20flow%20while%20creating%20paper%20losses%20that%20could%20offset%20their%20physician%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226871633d-7122-4e4d-9a0f-ef026f606d84%5C%22%3EWhat%20it%20takes%20to%20qualify%20for%20REPS%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20apply%20for%20REPS.%20You%20qualify%20based%20on%20how%20you%20spend%20your%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20main%20requirements%20must%20be%20met%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20must%20spend%20more%20than%20750%20hours%20a%20year%20on%20real-estate%20activities%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20your%20working%20hours%20must%20be%20in%20real%20estate%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20be%20an%20attorney%20working%2080%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20then%20claim%20REPS%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Green.%20%26quot%3BThat%20means%20you%20have%20to%20be%20working%20a%20minimum%20of%20160%20hours%20in%20real%20estate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20still%20works%20full%20time%20as%20a%20physician%2C%20while%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20builds%20custom%20closets%20and%20garages%20and%20manages%20their%20real%20estate%20portfolio%2C%20qualifies.%20%26quot%3BHis%20work%20was%20already%20considered%20REPS%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22dr.%20jill%20green%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69866348d3c7faef0ecdd719%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22758%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Green%20and%20her%20family.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dr.%20Jill%20Green%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDocumenting%20your%20hours%20is%20critical.%20CPA%20Kristel%20Espinosa%20warns%20that%20REPS%20can%20be%20closely%20scrutinized%20by%20the%20IRS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20have%20other%20jobs%2C%20but%20you%20just%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20show%20that%20to%20the%20IRS%20if%20ever%20audited%20that%20the%20real-estate%20business%20really%20is%20your%20main%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsakura%20logs%20his%20hours%20in%20a%20Google%20Calendar%20with%20detailed%20notes%2C%20everything%20from%20property%20visits%20to%20replacing%20an%20air%20conditioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d79d3f4-28cc-4832-aec0-4cf8b4603a37%5C%22%3EThe%20short-term%20rental%20workaround%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20neither%20spouse%20can%20qualify%20for%20REPS%2C%20or%20if%20you're%20a%20single%20household%20that%20doesn't%20qualify%2C%20there's%20another%20strategy%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bshort-term%20rental%20tax%20loophole.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IRS%20treats%20short-term%20rentals%20(where%20the%20average%20guest%20stay%20is%20seven%20days%20or%20fewer)%20differently.%20If%20the%20owner%20materially%20participates%20in%20managing%20the%20property%2C%20losses%20may%20be%20used%20to%20offset%20W-2%20income%2C%20even%20without%20REPS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20qualify%2C%20investors%20must%20meet%20one%20of%20several%20material%20participation%20requirements.%20The%20most%20common%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESpending%20at%20least%20500%20hours%20on%20the%20property%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpending%20at%20least%20100%20hours%2C%20and%20no%20one%20else%20spends%20more%20time%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpending%20more%20hours%20than%20everyone%20else%20combined%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20an%20investor%20spends%2080%20hours%20managing%20a%20short-term%20rental%20and%20cleaners%20and%20landscapers%20spend%2050%20hours%20total%2C%20the%20investor%20may%20still%20qualify%20under%20the%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%20everyone%20else%20combined%26quot%3B%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHan%20gives%20the%20example%20of%20someone%20earning%20%24500%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20W-2%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20invest%20in%20a%20long-term%20rental%20and%20you%20can't%20use%20it%20to%20offset%20the%20tax%2C%20then%20maybe%20you're%20paying%2037%25%20taxes%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20explained.%20However%2C%20if%20you%20turn%20that%20property%20into%20a%20short-term%20rental%20and%20generate%20a%20%24200%2C000%20tax%20loss%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20offsets%20your%20W-2%2C%20so%20maybe%20you're%20saving%20%2474%2C000%20in%20taxes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20%2425%2C000%20long-term%20rental%20allowance%2C%20this%20strategy%20has%20no%20income%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20people%20with%20lower%20income%2C%20it's%20even%20more%20impactful%2C%26quot%3B%20Han%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20make%20%241%20million%20and%20you%20save%20some%20tax%2C%20great.%20It's%20not%20life-changing.%20But%20if%20you're%20making%20%2480%2C000%20and%20you%20save%20a%20significant%20amount%20in%20taxes%2C%20that's%20a%20lot%20more%20money%20to%20invest%20for%20that%20specific%20taxpayer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-real-estate-professional-status-reps-works-marital-loophole-taxes-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771670701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998c314efb52c8bd0de96c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-real-estate-professional-status-reps-works-marital-loophole-taxes-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rule%2C%20which%20tax%20experts%20have%20nicknamed%20the%20%26quot%3Bmarital%20loophole%2C%26quot%3B%20allows%20qualifying%20investors%20to%20use%20real%20estate%20losses%20to%20offset%20W-2%20income.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-real-estate-professional-status-reps-works-marital-loophole-taxes-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20Killed%2C%206%20Injured%20As%20Bus%20Crashes%20Into%20Van%20In%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3A%20Cops%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Five%20people%20were%20killed%2C%20and%20six%20sustained%20serious%20injuries%20after%20a%20speeding%20bus%20crashed%20into%20their