ned%20the%20ongoing%20investigation%20into%20the%20plane%20crash%20that%20killed%20his%20uncle%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20potential%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20and%20irregularities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frohit-pawar-seeks-ministers-resignation-over-ajit-pawar-plane-crash-11117444%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20reasons%20dire%20economic%20predictions%20about%20Trump's%20policies%20haven't%20played%20out%2C%20according%20to%20one%20think%20tank%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224865%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20holding%20the%20tariff%20scheduled%20on%20%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e6512d5dbc4fd10daa68a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223244%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20warnings%2C%20Trump's%20policies%20have%20not%20caused%20a%20recession%20or%20a%20surge%20in%20inflation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Brookings%20Institution%20cites%20faulty%20economic%20models%20and%20offsetting%20policy%20impacts%20as%20key%20factors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20effects%20of%20trade%20and%20immigration%20policies%20are%20still%20unfolding%2C%20the%20think%20tank%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20economic%20policies%20have%20not%20led%20to%20the%20dire%20scenarios%20of%20recession%20or%20steep%20inflation%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-economists-academics-trade-policy-letter-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emany%20economists%20have%20warned%20about%20over%20the%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20new%20commentary%20from%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20major%20reasons%20that%20economists%20have%20so%20far%20gotten%20it%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20challenged%20the%20conventional%20economic%20norms%20in%20multiple%20ways%20that%20economists%20have%20warned%20would%20stress%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-today-tariffs-supreme-court-scotus-ruling-sp500-dow-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etariffs%20were%20struck%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%2C%20but%20experts%20spent%20the%20year%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20decision%20predicting%20dire%20consequences%20from%20the%20sweeping%20trade%20policy.%20For%20the%20most%20part%2C%20though%2C%20downbeat%20assessments%20of%20tariffs%20and%20other%20Trump%20policies%20haven't%20come%20to%20pass.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20used%20tariffs%20aggressively%20and%20cracked%20down%20on%20immigration%2C%20shrinking%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20yut%20the%20economy%20has%20mostly%20held%20strong%20with%20unemployment%20still%20historically%20low%20and%20consumers%20still%20spending.%20He's%20also%20tried%20to%20erode%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20independence%20and%20has%20added%20to%20the%20national%20debt%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks-to-buy-now-big-beautiful-bill-investing-ideas-socgen-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOne%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Interest%20rates%20haven't%20had%20a%20big%20reaction%20to%20either%20development%2C%20both%20of%20which%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20inflationary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Harris%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20director%20of%20Economic%20Studies%20at%20Brookings%2C%20put%20out%20some%20explanations%20for%20the%20discrepancies%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Brookings%20thinks%20everything%20has%20turned%20out%20better%20than%20some%20expected%20because%20the%20negative%20impacts%20of%20Trump's%20policies%20and%20actions%20were%20overestimated%20to%20begin%20with.%20The%20Fed%20is%20difficult%20to%20influence%2C%20tariffs%20aren't%20as%20steep%20as%20originally%20thought%2C%20and%20the%20pass-through%20to%20consumers%20has%20been%20smaller%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%20mainstream%20economic%20models%20are%20simply%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20possible%20the%20economics%20profession%20overstated%20the%20value%20of%20immigration%2C%20free%20trade%2C%20Fed%20independence%2C%20and%20a%20sustainable%20fiscal%20outlook%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20entirely%20possible%20that%20this%20volatile%20episode%20in%20American%20policymaking%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20greater%20understanding%20of%20the%20US%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThere%20could%20be%20one%20enduring%20lesson%E2%80%94learned%20both%20over%20the%20course%20of%202025%20as%20well%20as%20during%20the%20pandemic%E2%80%94that%20the%20size%20and%20diversity%20of%20the%20U.S.%20economy%20usually%20protects%20it%20from%20sharp%20downturns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecond%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20the%20positive%20fiscal%20impact%20of%20both%20the%20One%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%20Act%20%E2%80%94%20the%20GOP's%20landmark%20tax%20and%20spending%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20and%20of%20all%20the%20corporate%20spending%20on%20AI%20development.%20Harris%20pointed%20out%20that%20AI%20capex%20accounted%20for%2040%25%20of%20GDP%20in%202025%3B%20Goldman%20Sachs%20sees%20consumers'%20disposable%20incomes%20expanding%20by%200.4%25%20in%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%202026%20thanks%20to%20the%20OBBBA%3B%20and%20foreign%20investors%20have%20pledged%20to%20spend%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20the%20US%20amid%20Trump's%20trade%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThird%20and%20finally%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Harris%20said%20we%20may%20not%20have%20seen%20the%20final%20impact%20of%20Trump's%20policies%2C%20and%20it's%20still%20too%20early%20to%20issue%20a%20verdict%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20explanation%20is%20consistent%20with%20economic%20theory%20and%20evidence.%20The%20economic%20impact%20of%20curtailed%20immigration%20and%20mass%20deportations%20can%20take%20years%20to%20materialize%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20complexity%20of%20the%20FOMC's%20composition%20means%20that%20it%20may%20take%20years%20until%20we%20see%20the%20full%20impact%20of%20political%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20on%20tariffs%2C%20as%20we%20have%20heard%20from%20our%20western%20trading%20partners%20recently%20in%20Davos%2C%20only%20now%20have%20they%20begun%20to%20explore%20alternatives%20to%20the%20U.S.%20in%20terms%20of%20trade%20and%20investment%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-inflation-reasons-why-economic-predictions-were-wrong-brookings-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771669801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69977b54e1ba468a96ac587e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-inflation-reasons-why-economic-predictions-were-wrong-brookings-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20new%20commentary%20from%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20major%20reasons%20that%20economists%20have%20been%20wrong%20on%20Trump's%20policies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-inflation-reasons-why-economic-predictions-were-wrong-brookings-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kill%20Orders%20Against%20Khamenei%2C%20His%20Son%3A%20Report%20Flags%20Trump's%20Iran%20Options%22%2C%2