sstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20major%20focus%20of%20the%20India%20AI%20Impact%20Summit%20was%20to%20democratise%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI)%2C%20and%20the%20country%20has%20achieved%20that%20goal%2C%20S%20Krishnan%2C%20Secretary%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20(MeitY)%2C%20told%20NDTV.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwe-democratised-ai-meity-secretary-s-krishnan-to-ndtv-on-india-impact-summit-11117249%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20grew%20my%20tech%20income%20to%20over%20%24250%2C000%2C%20even%20though%20I%20never%20broke%20into%20Big%20Tech.%20This%20salary%20negotiation%20tip%20has%20never%20gone%20badly%20for%20me.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brian%20Jenney%20wearing%20a%20white%20shirt%2C%20standing%20on%20a%20golf%20course%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69947bfaa645d11881896e51%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJenney%20said%20he's%20learned%20how%20to%20play%20the%20salary%20negotiation%20game.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brian%20Jenney%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBrian%20Jenney%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-tips-big-tech-roles-2025-7%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreak%20into%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20his%20early%2030s%2C%20so%20he%20was%20naive%20about%20negotiating%20salaries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20Jenney%20learned%20to%20negotiate%20by%20asking%20for%2010%20to%2020%25%20more%20than%20his%20offer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThough%20he's%20never%20worked%20in%20Big%20Tech%2C%20he's%20earned%20more%20than%20he%20ever%20imagined.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Brian%20Jenney%2C%2042%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20California.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvice-on-how-to-land-big-tech-ai-job-education-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egot%20into%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20early%2030s%2C%20I%20had%20no%20clue%20how%20crazy%20lucrative%20the%20industry%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20as%20a%20web%20application%20developer%20in%202015%2C%20earning%20roughly%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I%20became%20savvier%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-people-make-negotiating-job-offer-from-salary-negotiator-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enegotiating%20my%20salary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20by%202023%2C%20I%20was%20making%20over%20%24250%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20earned%20more%20than%20I%20could%20have%20ever%20imagined%2C%20without%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreak-into-ai-microsoft-job-key-steps-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20in%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20people%20often%20assume%20the%20big%20money%20is%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20I've%20learned%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211f14ea2-aaf0-463b-a875-ba4e95f8d875%5C%22%3E1.%20It%20was%20dumb%20not%20to%20negotiate%20a%20starting%20salary%20because%20it%20already%20sounded%20impressive%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20have%20addiction%20issues%2C%20so%20I%20didn't%20really%20work%20from%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20to%2030%20and%20lost%20knowledge%20that%20people%20gain%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-ceo-mustafa-suleyman-white-collar-tasks-automation-prediction-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhite%20collar%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20this%20stage%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20naive%20about%20the%20salary%20potential%20of%20my%20industry%2C%20and%20when%20people%20in%20tech%20said%20they%20were%20on%20%24150%2C000%2C%20it%20blew%20my%20mind%2C%20and%20I%20began%20to%20feel%20underpaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20after%20two%20years%20in%20the%20web%20developer%20role%2C%20I%20landed%20a%20job%20at%20a%20startup.%20I%20was%20so%20impressed%20when%20I%20was%20offered%20%24120%2C000%20that%20I%20didn't%20negotiate%20my%20salary%2C%20which%20was%20dumb%20in%20retrospect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20environment%20was%20extremely%20fast-paced%20and%20high-caliber.%20I%20struggled%20with%20imposter%20syndrome%20as%20one%20of%20the%20team's%20more%20junior%20members.%20I%20felt%20like%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20developers%20there%20and%20that%20I%20was%20already%20being%20paid%20more%20than%20I%20deserved.%20It%20discouraged%20me%20from%20asking%20for%20a%20raise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20I%20joined%20the%20media%20intelligence%20company%20Zignal%20Labs.%20I%20was%20so%20happy%20about%20the%20job%20offer%20that%20I%20didn't%20negotiate%20the%20salary%2C%20so%20my%20pay%20initially%20stayed%20roughly%20the%20same%20as%20in%20my%20previous%20job.%20It%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20plateaued%2C%20even%20though%20I%20had%20more%20money%20than%20I%20needed.%20An%20unfortunate%20symptom%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhottest-job-in-tech-writing-words-ai-hiring-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20in%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20that%20you%20get%20drawn%20to%20wanting%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChoosing%20this%20role%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20right%20move%2C%20though.%20I%20had%20more%20room%20to%20grow%20and%20was%20in%20a%20better%20learning%20environment%20at%20a%20larger%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20tech%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-hiring-fell-hard-after-covid-these-jobs-survived-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehiring%20spree%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202020%2C%20my%20peers%20said%20they%20were%20getting%20crazy%20offers%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20miss%20out.%20That%20August%2C%20I%20joined%20The%20Clorox%20Company%2C%20a%20manufacturing%20firm%2C%20as%20a%20software%20engineer.%20By%202023%2C%20I%20was%20making%20over%20%24250%2C000%3A%20the%20peak%20of%20my%20earnings%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20I%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20and%20I've%20continued%20to%20work%20in%20various%20software%20engineering%20roles.%20I%20bought%20a%20business%20in%202023%2C%20and%20my%20focus%20has%20shifted%20to%20seeking%20out%20flexibility%20and%20time%20to%20build%20it%2C%20instead%20of%20maximizing%20corporate%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202e61c69-f475-4560-af13-9c517f056653%5C%22%3E2.%20I%20prepare%20for%20the%20pressure%20of%20job%20interviews%20by%20practicing%20with%20strangers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInterviews%20are%20like%20a%20carnival%20game%20where%20you%20can%20win%20big%20money%20by%20performing%20well%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20get%20to%20the%20negotiation%20stage%20without%20passing%20them.%20They're%20structured%2C%20learnable%2C%20and%20winnable%20with%20the%20right%20preparation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20have%20job%20interviews%20lined%20up%2C%20I%20do%20technical%20practice%20and%20use%20a%20platform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pramp.com%2F%23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20Pramp%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20pairs%20you%20with%20strangers%20for%20practice%20interviews.%20I've%20found%20this%20helps%20simulate%20the%20nerves%20and%20pressure%20of%20real%20interviews%20better%20than%20practicing%20with%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20try%20to%20do%20at%20least%20two%20mock%20interviews%20before%20an%20interview%20I%20really%20care%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brian%20Jenney%20is%20standing%20on%20a%20stage%20giving%20a%20talk.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699482bde1ba468a96ac2693%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJenney%20uses%20a%20platform%20called%20Pramp%20to%20practice%20job%20interviews.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brian%20Jenney%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222134895f-b9de-406b-bf8c-031df35d8c6b%5C%22%3E3.%20I%20learned%20to%20'play%20the%20game'%20of%20salary%20negotiation.%20Now%20I%20ask%20for%20at%20least%2010%25%20more.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I've%20benefited%20a%20lot%20from%20people%20in%20tech%20being%20open%20about%20their%20salaries%20and%20career%20paths%2C%20which%20helped%20me%20understand%20what%20was%20possible%20and%20gave%20me%20confidence%20to%20negotiate%20and%20aim%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquadrupled-salary-big-tech-job-hopping-negotiating-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esalary%20negotiation%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20game%20you%20have%20to%20play%2C%20and%20if%20you%20don't%2C%20you%20lose%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20consistently%20negotiating%20pay%20in%20the%20late%202010s.%20I%20usually%20tell%20the%20employer%20that%20I'm%20really%20excited%20to%20start%20the%20job%2C%20but%20that%20I%20was%20hoping%20to%20come%20in%20at%20a%20higher%20salary%20range%2C%20usually%2010%20to%2020%25%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20this%20to%20be%20very%20effective%2C%20and%20it%20has%20never%20gone%20badly%20for%20me.%20If%20an%20employer%20sounds%20firm%20on%20their%20offer%2C%20I%20usually%20try%20to%20explore%20whether%20a%20sign-on%20bonus%20is%20possible%20instead%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20push%20aggressively%20beyond%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2210920775-410f-4a0b-8fbe-3d653b78a223%5C%22%3EI%20have%20more%20money%20than%20I%20need%2C%20even%20though%20I%20never%20worked%20in%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brian%20Jenney%20is%20pointing%20at%20a%20wall%20with%20computer%20code%20written%20on%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699482cba645d11881896f15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJenney%20said%20a%20salary%20of%20%24150%2C000%20is%20more%20than%20enough%20for%20him.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Brian%20Jenney%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20interviewed%20with%20but%20never%20been%20hired%20by%20the%20Big%20Tech%20companies.%20Besides%2C%20I%20like%20working%20at%20smaller%20startups%20and%20non-tech%20companies%20where%20I%20think%20you%20can%20have%20a%20greater%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-salaries-compensation-data-ai-talent-wars-silicon-valley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20going%20to%20%26quot%3Bbeat%20me%26quot%3B%20on%20pay%20because%20their%20stock%20compensation%20will%20outpace%20my%20earnings.%20But%20I%20see%20my%20current%20lifestyle%20as%20comparable%20to%20theirs.%20I%20believe%20there's%20a%20reason%20software%20engineers%20aren't%20driving%20around%20Mountain%20View%20in%20Ferraris%3A%20they%20can't%20cash%20out%20all%20their%20stock%20money%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20always%20more%20you%20can%20earn%2C%20but%20when%20my%20salary%20hit%20the%20%24150%2C000%20mark%2C%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20more%20than%20I%20needed.%20I'd%20rather%20prioritize%20jobs%20where%20I'm%20happy%2C%20I'm%20learning%2C%20and%20I%20can%20cover%20my%20needs%20while%20still%20saving.%20That's%20all%20I%20really%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20growing%20your%20salary%20in%20tech%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20