wever%2C%20say%20that%20they're%20quitting%20the%20apps%20and%20looking%20for%20alternative%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustles-entrepreneurship-cost-to-start-small-business-capitalism-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eside%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20finding%20full-time%20work%2C%20if%20they%20were%20full-time%20gig%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Howe%20spent%20about%20two%20years%20working%20full-time%20as%20an%20Uber%20driver%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-denver-for-quieter-life-still-love-visiting-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDenver%20area%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20losing%20his%20job.%20Initially%2C%20he%20said%2C%20he%20could%20work%20about%2040%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20accepting%20every%20trip%20that%20the%20Uber%20app%20offered%20him%2C%20and%20earn%20between%20%242%2C000%20and%20%243%2C000%20in%20gross%20pay%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20good-paying%20trips%20became%20more%20scarce%20in%20his%20area%2C%20though%2C%20Howe%20said%20that%20he%20started%20cherrypicking%20the%20most%20profitable%20ones%2C%20a%20strategy%20that%20involved%20a%20lot%20more%20unpaid%20time%20watching%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-ads-launches-intelligence-insights-trips-takeout-data-marketers-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20trip%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20wound%20up%20spending%20a%20lot%20more%20time%20on%20the%20app%2C%20even%20though%20you%20weren't%20necessarily%20driving%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20last%20year%2C%20Howe%20took%20a%20full-time%20job%20in%20finance%20after%20one%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-drivers-worst-passengers-rude-no-tip-stop-drive-thru-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber%20passengers%3C%2Fa%3E%20recommended%20him%20for%20the%20position.%20He%20hasn't%20driven%20for%20Uber%20since%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20working%20long%20hours%2C%20Howe%20said%20that%20he's%20worried%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-ceo-autonomous-cars-must-meet-higher-safety-standard-humans-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eself-driving%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%20displacing%20human%20drivers.%20%26quot%3BThe%20future%20looks%20quite%20grim%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f04af565-e8d6-4e45-a042-ffc364596843%5C%22%3EMany%20Uber%2C%20Lyft%20drivers%20leave%20after%206%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2041%25%20of%20Uber%20drivers%20who%20started%20working%20on%20the%20app%20between%20July%20and%20September%202025%20were%20still%20completing%20trips%20on%20the%20app%20six%20months%20later%2C%20according%20to%20Gridwise%2C%20a%20data%20analytics%20company%20that%20analyzed%20app%20usage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20data%20on%20people%20who%20began%20driving%20for%20Uber%20between%20January%20and%20April%202024%20found%20that%20about%2050%25%20of%20workers%20were%20still%20using%20the%20app%20after%20six%20months.%20Lyft's%20retention%20rate%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20hovered%20around%2040%25%20in%20both%20data%20sets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Uber%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20said%20that%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bsaw%20historic%20low%20rates%20of%20driver%20churn%20in%20the%20US%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20last%20year.%20Uber%20also%20pointed%20to%20a%20survey%20released%20last%20year%20that%20found%2064%25%20of%20its%20drivers%20reported%20being%20%26quot%3Bsatisfied%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bvery%20satisfied%26quot%3B%20with%20their%20experience%20on%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Ryan%20Green%2C%20CEO%20of%20Gridwise%2C%20said%20that%20many%20gig%20apps%20used%20to%20pay%20more%20in%20bonuses%2C%20such%20as%20extra%20pay%20for%20completing%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20trips.%20That%20extra%20pay%2C%20which%20the%20apps%20offered%20during%20and%20immediately%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20kept%20many%20drivers%20completing%20trips%20and%20delivering%20orders.%20Since%20then%2C%20drivers%20have%20received%20fewer%20of%20those%20bonuses%2C%20Green%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20more%20people%20have%20turned%20to%20the%20gig%20apps%20to%20make%20money%20after%20layoffs%20or%20as%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20rises%2C%20making%20them%20more%20competitive%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20market's%20been%20oversupplied%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriven-for-uber-decade-dont-know-what-my-future-holds-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUber%20driver%20in%20Atlanta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20relied%20on%20the%20app%20for%20income%20for%20a%20decade%20after%20losing%20her%20corporate%20job%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20this%20past%20fall%20that%20she%20was%20looking%20for%20other%20work%20options%20after%20her%20ride-hailing%20earnings%20fell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Fisher%2C%20who%20works%20as%20a%20ride-hailing%20driver%20for%20Uber%20and%20delivers%20for%20DoorDash%20in%20Houston%2C%20said%20he's%20looking%20for%20other%20job%20opportunities%20after%20Uber%20temporarily%20deactivated%20his%20account%20for%20not%20completing%20an%20identity%20check%20through%20the%20app%20in%20time.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoordash-walmart-spark-gig-workers-share-weirdest-deactivation-stories-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAccount%20deactivations%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20common%20for%20gig%20workers%2C%20and%20the%20companies%20don't%20always%20provide%20a%20clear%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFisher%2C%20who%20worked%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20restaurant%20management%20before%20becoming%20a%20gig%20worker%2C%20said%20the%20deactivation%20highlighted%20the%20precarious%20nature%20of%20gig%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20making%20it%20very%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20have%20a%20stable%20income%2C%20because%20I%20don't%20know%20for%20sure%20whether%20they're%20going%20to%20deactivate%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe8fe49a-fee3-4022-94ba-4154fe5883c8%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%209-to-5%20job%20after%20gig%20work%20can%20be%20hard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20an%20alternative%20to%20gig%20work%2C%20especially%20a%20regular%20full-time%20job%2C%20isn't%20easy%20right%20now.%20Many%20workers%20who%20have%20quit%20their%20jobs%20or%20been%20laid%20off%20are%20facing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-get-job-long-term-unemployed-job-seekers-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-term%20unemployment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eas%20they%20try%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20network%20and%20interview%20for%20a%20new%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Lyft%20driver%20in%20Florida%20pointed%20to%20another%20issue%3A%20Having%20gig%20work%20as%20the%20most%20recent%20work%20experience%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20can%20make%20landing%20a%20new%20role%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20driver%2C%20who%20has%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20and%20ran%20his%20own%20marketing%20business%20before%20becoming%20a%20ride-hailing%20driver%2C%20said%20he%20thinks%20the%20year%20he's%20spent%20as%20a%20Lyft%20driver%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20most%20of%20his%20job%20applications%20don't%20lead%20to%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20much%20considering%20taking%20Lyft%20off%20of%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20I%20do%20that%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20show%20an%20enormous%20gap%20of%20employment%20that%20I'm%20going%20to%20need%20to%20explain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20how%20I'm%20going%20to%20go%20about%20doing%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20driver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3